panic. Where you get a discount. 

185
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:51,600
You wouldn't want to sell at obvious 
resistance. Not enough buyers. You'd  

186
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:59,200
want to sell above resistance. Where retail 
traders chase. Where you get premium prices.

187
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:01,520
The Shakeout Strategy
Stop losses cluster at obvious  

188
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:08,560
levels. Just below support. Just above 
resistance. Below yesterday's low. Above  

189
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:16,000
yesterday's high. These clusters create liquidity 
pools that smart money targets deliberately. 

190
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:21,840
Again, think like a market maker for a second. 
You need to buy 10 million shares without  

191
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:28,400
spiking the price. Where do you find sellers? 
You create them by triggering stop losses. 

192
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:35,360
Push price below support, trigger the stops, 
buy the shares from panicking traders. Then let  

193
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:42,560
price recover. You've filled your order at great 
prices while retail traders nurse their losses. 

194
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:49,360
This isn't illegal. It's not cheating. It's 
understanding market mechanics. Stop losses are  

195
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:55,600
visible to market makers through order flow. 
They know exactly where the liquidity sits.  

196
00:18:55,600 --> 00:19:01,840
They'd be foolish not to use this information.
Smart money loves shakeouts. These are their  

197
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:06,720
favorite tools. It's how smart 
money are collecting cheap prices. 

198
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:12,080
Once they collect enough positions, they 
stop selling pressure. Price bounces back  

199
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:18,160
above support. The shakeout is complete.
Small traders watch in frustration. They  

200
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:23,040
got stopped out at the low. Now 
price is moving up without them. 

201
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:27,360
This happens every single 
day. At every major level. 

202
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:31,120
The solution is to trade 
the shakeout, not the level. 

203
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:34,640
When you see price break below 
support with a long shadow,  

204
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:41,280
that's your signal. Smart money just collected 
liquidity. They want price higher now. 

205
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:48,000
When you see price break above resistance then 
immediately fail, that's your signal. Smart money  

206
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:57,180
just distributed. They want price lower now.
Again. Trade with the shakeout. Not against it.

207
00:19:57,180 --> 00:19:59,440
The Direction Secret
Most traders try to predict where  

208
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:06,400
price will stop. They look for resistance 
to sell. Support to buy. Reversal points. 

209
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:10,160
This is backwards thinking.
Instead of predicting where price  

210
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:16,800
will stop, trade where price wants to go.
Look at the most recent high or low. That  

211
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:24,240
tells you the current bias. New high means 
bullish bias. New low means bearish bias. 

212
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:30,480
Trade in that direction. Not against it.
If price just made a new high,  

213
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:37,520
look for pullbacks to buy. Don't look for 
resistance to sell. The bias is up. Trade up. 

214
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:42,240
If price just made a new low, look 
for bounces to sell. Don't look for  

215
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:50,560
support to buy. The bias is down. Trade down.
This simple shift changes everything. You stop  

216
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:57,280
fighting the momentum. You start trading with it.
Here's what this looks like in practice. Price  

217
00:20:57,280 --> 00:21:03,360
breaks to new highs. Instead of looking for where 
it might reverse, look for where it might pull  

218
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:11,280
back. That pullback is your buy opportunity.
Price breaks to new lows. Instead of looking  

219
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:18,960
for where it might bounce, look for where it might 
retrace. That retrace is your sell opportunity. 

220
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:24,400
You're trading the direction of the 
most recent momentum. Not against it. 

221
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:31,252
This keeps you on the right side of the 
market. The side where smart money operates.

222
00:21:31,252 --> 00:21:33,360
The Order Flow at Key Levels
If you understand the orders behind  

223
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:39,120
price movement, this will change everything 
about how you see support and resistance. 

224
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:46,880
At every price level, limit orders wait on both 
sides. Buy limits below market price. Sell limits  

225
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:53,520
above. When price reaches these levels, the 
battle begins. More buy orders than sell  

226
00:21:53,520 --> 00:22:01,520
orders means price might bounce. More sell orders 
than buy orders means price might break through. 

227
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:07,200
But here's what retail traders miss - smart 
money can see order flow depth that you  

228
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:15,520
can't. They know if support has 10,000 contracts 
waiting or 1 million. They position accordingly. 

229
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:22,240
The solution is to monitor the footprint 
charts or Level 2 data. You can see orders  

230
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:28,640
appear and disappear at key levels. A 
huge buy order appears at support means  

231
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:34,560
someone's defending. If that order gets 
pulled, then support is about to break. 

232
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:41,040
This is why the same support level might hold 
five times then break on the sixth. The order  

233
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:49,659
flow changed. The defender left. Without those buy 
orders, support becomes just a line on a chart.

234
00:22:49,659 --> 00:22:51,440
The Round Number Edge
Some of the most reliable support  

235
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:57,680
and resistance levels have nothing to do with 
technical analysis. They appear at round numbers  

236
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:03,040
because human psychology makes them significant.
Round numbers are important  

237
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:08,160
for smart money traders.
Look at any chart. Major reversals happen  

238
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:16,000
at round numbers. The level ends in 50 or 100.
All this human behavior creates real  

239
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,640
order flow at round numbers.
Smart money knows this. They know  

240
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:28,560
retail traders cluster orders around these levels. 
So they use round numbers as liquidity zones. 

241
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:34,240
Here's how it works. Price approaches a 
major round number. Retail traders start  

242
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:41,360
thinking about taking profits. Or entering new 
positions. Orders pile up around that level. 

243
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:47,600
Smart money sees this buildup. They know they 
can fill large positions at these levels.  

244
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:53,200
So they push price toward the round number.
But here's what separates professionals from  

245
00:23:53,200 --> 00:24:00,080
amateurs - smart money positions themselves 
just before the round numbers, not at them. 

246
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:09,520
They'll buy Tesla at $290, knowing retail traders 
are waiting to buy at $300. When price hits the  

247
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:15,520
round number, retail buying provides the 
liquidity for smart money to take profits. 

248
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:23,360
Sometimes price stops just short. Smart money 
absorbs all the selling. Then pushes price higher. 

249
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:30,480
Sometimes price breaks through. Smart money 
absorbs all the buying. Then pulls price back. 

250
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:34,720
Either way, they get their 
fills. They get their liquidity. 

251
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:41,200
The key for you is recognizing these zones 
early. Before the obvious action happens. 

252
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:48,560
When price approaches a major round number, get 
ready. Big moves often start from these levels. 

253
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:51,760
But don't trade the obvious 
play. Don't buy the break  

254
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:55,760
above key level. Don't sell the rejection at it. 

255
00:24:55,760 --> 00:25:02,400
Wait for the shakeout. Wait for smart money 
to show their hand. Then follow their lead.

256
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,800
The Complete System
Now you know how they think. How they  

